description.purpose:
Checks that transacting against a contract, whose function calls into another contract, and both functions emit an event, works correctly. Specifically, that the transaction receipt logs shows both events, and that they can be extracted correctly from the receipt.
The contract call goes EventEmitterCaller.callEmitSimpleEvent -> EventEmitter.emitSimpleEvent. In this case msg.sender in EventEmitterCaller is the account that performs the transaction, whereas msg.sending in EventEmitter is the address of the EventEmitterCaller contract. The events are defined as;
CallerSimpleEvent(uint indexed id, string message, address indexed sender) SimpleEvent(uint indexed id, string message, address indexed sender);
